paragraphs.title: Let us first read the 311 complaint data for new york city from hDFS
paragraphs.text:
val nyc_sdff = 
sqlContext.read.format("com.databricks.spark.csv").option("header","true").load("hdfs://localhost:9000/datasets/nyc-311-service/311_Service_Requests_from_2010_to_Present.csv").cache()

result.msg: nyc_sdff: org.apache.spark.sql.DataFrame = [Unique Key: string, Created Date: string, Closed Date: string, Agency: string, Agency Name: string, Complaint Type: string, Descriptor: string, Location Type: string, Incident Zip: string, Incident Address: string, Street Name: string, Cross Street 1: string, Cross Street 2: string, Intersection Street 1: string, Intersection Street 2: string, Address Type: string, City: string, Landmark: string, Facility Type: string, Status: string, Due Date: string, Resolution Description: string, Resolution Action Updated Date: string, Community Board: string, Borough: string, X Coordinate (State Plane): string, Y Coordinate (State Plane): string, Park Facility Name: string, Park Borough: string, School Name: string, School Number: string, School Region: s...

paragraphs.title: Create a Temporary Spark Table out of the Spark DataFrame
paragraphs.text: nyc_sdff.registerTempTable("nyc311f")

paragraphs.title: Total 311 Complaints in New York City In last 1 year
paragraphs.text: %sql select count(*) as TotalComplaintCountFrom2015 from nyc311f

result.msg:
TotalComplaintCountFrom2015
1652212

paragraphs.title: Let us see what is Heating Complaints Count Zip Code wise on every day basis
paragraphs.text:
%sql 
select split(`Created Date`, ' ')[0] as Incident_Date, `Incident Zip` as Incident_Zip, count(`Unique Key`) as HeatingComplaintCount  from nyc311f where `Complaint Type` = "HEAT/HOT WATER" group by split(`Created Date`, ' ')[0], `Incident Zip` order by count(`Unique Key`) desc limit 10

paragraphs.title: Let us create SparkR Data Farmes for Heating Complaint Count and Street Complaint Count for each zip code on every day basis
paragraphs.text:
%spark.r

nyc_heatf <- sql(sqlContext, "select split(`Created Date`, ' ')[0] as Incident_Date, `Incident Zip` as Incident_Zip, count(`Unique Key`) as HeatingComplaintCount from nyc311f where `Complaint Type` = 'HEAT/HOT WATER' group by split(`Created Date`, ' ')[0], `Incident Zip`")
registerTempTable(nyc_heatf, "nycheatf")
nyc_streetf <- sql(sqlContext, "select split(`Created Date`, ' ')[0] as Incident_Date, `Incident Zip` as Incident_Zip, count(`Unique Key`) as StreetComplaintCount from nyc311f where `Complaint Type` = 'Street Condition' group by split(`Created Date`, ' ')[0], `Incident Zip`")
registerTempTable(nyc_streetf, "nycstreetf")
nyc_top <- sql(sqlContext, "select a1.Incident_Date as IncidentDay, cast(a1.Incident_Zip as STRING) as Zip, cast(a1.HeatingComplaintCount as BIGINT) as HeatingCount, cast(b1.StreetComplaintCount as BIGINT) as StreetProblemCount from nycheatf a1, nycstreetf b1 where a1.Incident_Zip = b1.Incident_Zip and a1.Incident_Date = b1.Incident_Date")
registerTempTable(nyc_top, "nyctopf")

result.msg:
nyc_heatf <- sql(sqlContext, "select split(`Created Date`, ' ')[0] as Incident_Date, `Incident Zip` as Incident_Zip, count(`Unique Key`) as HeatingComplaintCount from nyc311f where `Complaint Type` = 'HEAT/HOT WATER' group by split(`Created Date`, ' ')[0], `Incident Zip`")


registerTempTable(nyc_heatf, "nycheatf")


nyc_streetf <- sql(sqlContext, "select split(`Created Date`, ' ')[0] as Incident_Date, `Incident Zip` as Incident_Zip, count(`Unique Key`) as StreetComplaintCount from nyc311f where `Complaint Type` = 'Street Condition' group by split(`Created Date`, ' ')[0], `Incident Zip`")


registerTempTable(nyc_streetf, "nycstreetf")


nyc_top <- sql(sqlContext, "select a1.Incident_Date as IncidentDay, cast(a1.Incident_Zip as STRING) as Zip, cast(a1.HeatingComplaintCount as BIGINT) as HeatingCount, cast(b1.StreetComplaintCount as BIGINT) as StreetProblemCount from nycheatf a1, nycstreetf b1 where a1.Incident_Zip = b1.Incident_Zip and a1.Incident_Date = b1.Incident_Date")


registerTempTable(nyc_top, "nyctopf")

paragraphs.title: Let us use R Visualization Component for Day wise Visualization of the Complaints
paragraphs.text:
%spark.knitr results='asis'

library(googleVis) 

nyc_top_local <- take(nyc_top, nrow(nyc_top))
nyc_top_local$IncidentDt <- as.Date(nyc_top_local$IncidentDay, format = "%m/%d/%Y")
nyc_top_local$IncidentDay <- NULL

options(gvis.plot.tag='chart')
NYC_Complaint <- gvisMotionChart(nyc_top_local, idvar="Zip", timevar="IncidentDt", options=list(width=1000, height=600))
